reviewText: Bought this set at Walmart for only $5.00 today.  Have not seen all of the movies yet, and looking forward to it.  Of course there are some cheesy scenes presented within the movies, but that's what makes it fun to watch.  Parents and Fido are two I have not watched in a long time, so my memory is a little fuzzy on some of the scenes.  There is a lot of gore in some of these movies if that's a person sort of thing.  Why, "Earth Girls Are Easy" is in this collection is kind of weird though. Boy Eats Girl is kind of a sad teen flick, though it has some good parts.  All in all, the price was great and I'am not complaining.
summary: Some Okay Movies, but Consider A Great Value Elsewhere

reviewText: I happened to stumble upon this DVD at local Walmart for $5.00! That is a great price for six movies. I'm surprised to find that Lionsgate released the unrated version of Bloody Diner instead of the R version.The movies on this two discs set are:Disc 1:Bloody Diner (Unrated;1987; 88 minutes)Earth Girls Are Easy (PG; 1988; 99 minutes)Boy Eats Girl (R; 2005; 80 minutes)Disc 2:Parents (R; 1989; 81 minutes)Sundown: The Vampire in Retreat (R; 1990; 104 minutes)Fido (R; 2006; 92 minutes)

reviewText: A collection of six movies, mostly from the Vestron Video vault. The reason to pick up this set is to get Parents and Blood Diner! reviewText: some of the movies I had seen before but it was cheeper to buy this then buy all these movies....also I could not find them to rent .most of these movies are not very good. earth girls are easy is an ok movie with jim carry.I bought this for the movie "fido" . funny & kind of cute zombie movie about a 70's family who has a pet zombie.I also wanted to see "boy eats girl" not a good movie but still wanted to watch it.this is one of the better horror movie collections that I have seen.

reviewText: Blood Diner is presented here for the first time on DVD. As far as I can tell it is the original uncut version. All the films on this set are widescreen with the exception of Sundown, which is a shame, because it looks awful in fullscreen. Parents fits in well with Blood Diner, but why Earth Girls Are Easy is on this set is beyond me. No bonus features.
